import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}><MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"home"}}>{`Home`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`This site demonstrates some basic components that I use to put together websites. Components can be configured using props that are listed
in a table below each sample component. In lieu of specific properties, most components have certain defaults to match a style I've used previously on a site.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`You can manually edit the code for each component to play around and see what happens.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`It uses `}<MDXTag name="a" components={components} parentName="p" props={{"href":"https://github.com/tachyons-css/tachyons-system"}}>{`tachyons-system`}</MDXTag>{`, `}<MDXTag name="a" components={components} parentName="p" props={{"href":"https://www.styled-components.com/"}}>{`styled-components`}</MDXTag>{` and `}<MDXTag name="a" components={components} parentName="p" props={{"href":"https://jxnblk.com/styled-system/"}}>{`styled-system`}</MDXTag>{` under the hood together with `}<MDXTag name="a" components={components} parentName="p" props={{"href":"https://www.docz.site/"}}>{`Docz`}</MDXTag>{` (with a custom theme).`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
